ENTRY            F0736   20260225   20260508   20260508       F108
SUBENT        F0736001   20260225   20260508   20260508       F108
BIB                 13         43
TITLE      Vector analysing power of (d,p) reactions on 16O and
           24Mg at 12 MeV
AUTHOR     (R.C.Brown,I.Govil,J.A.R.Griffith,G.Hudson,O.Karban,
           S.Roman)
INSTITUTE  (2UK BIR)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,185,49,1972)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2UK BIR)
INC-SOURCE (POLIS) A beam of 12.3 MeV purely vector polarized
           deuterons initiated (d,p) reactions in targets placed
           in the main scattering chamber.
DETECTOR   (TELES,SIBAR) Four silicon surface-barrier detector
            telescopes
SAMPLE     The oxygen target was a 1.3 mg/cm2 thick foil of
           cellulose acetate (C7H16O9), and the magnesium target
           consisted of a 4 mg/cm2 metallic strip enriched to
           99.7% 24Mg.
MONITOR    (2-HE-4(D,EL)2-HE-4,,DA) The polarimeter was cross
           calibrated against the VAP at 45 degr.(lab), which
           was taken to be 0.38 for 8.96 MeV mid-target energy.
           The gas polarimeter contained 2.2 mg/cm2 of helium.
           The scattered deuterons were detected at 45 degr.
           with +-1 degr. extreme angular acceptances. The
           additional uncertainty on the VAP of the reaction which
           is believed to be +-3%.
           (6-C-12(D,P)6-C-13,,POL/DA) The beam polarization was
           measured by a polarimeter employing the reaction. The
           polarimeter consisted of a 7 mm wide strip of
           12.5 mg/cm2 thick polyethylene, viewed by silicon
           detectors at +-57 degr.(lab) with extreme angular
           acceptances of +-9 degr.
           The asymmetries in these polarimeters were in both case
           related to the VAP of the reaction at 60 degr.(lab)
           measured simultaneously in the main chamber with a
           5.5 mg/cm2 polyethylene target.
MONIT-REF  (,A.Trier+,J,PRL,18,915,1967)
           (,J.A.R.Griffith+,J,NP/A,146,193,1970)
ADD-RES    (COMP) The experimental data are compared with results
           of DWBA calculations made in the spherical
           approximation and also with allowance for nuclear
           deformation. The optical model.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Statistical error
HISTORY    (20050928C)
           (20260225U) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              43
COMMON               4          3
EN         ANG-RSL    ANG-ERR-D  ERR-DIG
MEV        ADEG       ADEG       NO-DIM
       12.3        1.5        0.3      0.010
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           50
SUBENT        F0736002   20260225   20260508   20260508       F108
BIB                  3          3
REACTION   (8-O-16(D,P)8-O-17,PAR,POL/DA,,VAP)
STATUS     (CURVE,,R.C.Brown+,J,NP/A,185,49,1972) Figs 1-3
HISTORY    (20260225U) SD: STATUS updated.
ENDBIB               3
